{"article_id":"8yFYS8uC2V734b11","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"A majority of Supreme Court justices voiced skepticism Wednesday about the legitimacy of a federal provision","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"that prevents married gay couples from receiving a range of federal benefits ,","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"raising questions","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"about whether the Defense of Marriage Act will stand .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"The court concluded arguments early Wednesday afternoon on the challenge to the Defense of Marriage Act provision","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"that defines marriage as between a man and a woman .","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"The hearing was the second in back-to-back gay marriage cases before the court this week ,","depth":4},{"id":7,"text":"both of which have attracted intense public interest .","depth":4},{"id":8,"text":"In the two-hour hearing Wednesday , Justice Anthony Kennedy , often the decisive vote in close cases , joined the four more liberal justices","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"in raising questions about the provision of the federal Defense of Marriage Act","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"that is being challenged .","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"Kennedy said","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"the law appears to intrude on the power of states","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"that have chosen to recognize same-sex marriages .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"Other justices said","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"the law creates what Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg called two classes of marriage , full marriage and `` skim-milk marriage . ''","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"The motivation behind the 1996 federal law ,","depth":12},{"id":17,"text":"passed by large majorities in Congress","depth":13},{"id":18,"text":"and signed by President Bill Clinton ,","depth":13},{"id":19,"text":"was questioned repeatedly by Justice Elena Kagan .","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"She read from a House of Representatives report","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"explaining","depth":13},{"id":22,"text":"that the reason for the law was `` to express moral disapproval of homosexuality . ''","depth":13},{"id":23,"text":"The quote produced an audible reaction in the courtroom .","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"Paul Clement ,","depth":13},{"id":25,"text":"representing the House Republican leadership","depth":14},{"id":26,"text":"in defending the law ,","depth":14},{"id":27,"text":"said","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"the more relevant question is whether Congress had `` any rational basis for the statute . ''","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"He supplied one , the federal government 's interest","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"in treating same-sex couples the same","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"no matter where they live .","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"Clement said","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"the government does not want military families `` to resist transfer from West Point to Fort Sill","depth":14},{"id":34,"text":"because they 're going to lose their benefits . ''","depth":14},{"id":35,"text":"The U.S. Military Academy at West Point is in New York ,","depth":14},{"id":36,"text":"where same-sex marriage is legal ,","depth":14},{"id":37,"text":"and Fort Sill is in Oklahoma ,","depth":14},{"id":38,"text":"where gay marriages are not legal .","depth":14},{"id":39,"text":"The law affects a range of benefits","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"available to married couples ,","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"including tax breaks , survivor benefits and health insurance for spouses of federal employees .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"It also is possible the court could dismiss the case for procedural reasons ,","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"though that prospect seemed less likely","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"than it did in Tuesday 's argument over gay marriage in California .","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"Marital status is relevant in more than 1,100 federal laws","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"that include estate taxes , Social Security survivor benefits and health benefits for federal employees .","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"Lawsuits around the country have led four federal district courts and two appeals courts to strike down the law 's Section 3 ,","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"which defines marriage .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"In 2011 , the Obama administration abandoned its defense of the law","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"but continues to enforce it .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"House Republicans are now defending DOMA in the courts .","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"The justices chose for their review the case of Edith Windsor , 83 , of New York ,","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"who sued","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"to challenge a $ 363,000 federal estate tax bill","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"after her partner of 44 years died in 2009 .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"Windsor ,","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"who goes by Edie ,","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"married Thea Spyer in 2007 in Canada","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"after doctors told them","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"that Spyer would not live much longer .","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"She suffered from multiple sclerosis for many years .","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"Spyer left everything","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"she had","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"to Windsor .","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"There is no dispute","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"if Windsor had been married to a man ,","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"her estate tax bill would have been zero .","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"The U.S. 2nd Circuit Court of Appeals in New York agreed with a district judge","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"that the provision of DOMA deprived Windsor of the constitutional guarantee of equal protection of the law .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"Like the Proposition 8 case from California , Windsor 's lawsuit could falter on a legal technicality","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"without a definitive ruling from the high court .","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"The House Republicans , the Obama administration and a lawyer","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"appointed by the court","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"were to spend part of the hearing","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"discussing","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"whether the House Republican leadership can defend the law in court","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"because the administration decided not to ,","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"and whether the administration forfeited its right","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"to participate in the case","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"because it changed its position","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"and now argues","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"that the provision is unconstitutional .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"If the Supreme Court finds","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"that it does not have the authority","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"to hear the case ,","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"Windsor probably would still get her refund","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"because she won in the lower courts .","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"But there would be no definitive decision about the law from the nation 's highest court ,","depth":6},{"id":90,"text":"and it would remain on the books .","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"On Tuesday , the justices weighed a fundamental issue :","depth":4},{"id":92,"text":"Does the Constitution require","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"that people be allowed to marry whom they choose ,","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"regardless of either partner 's gender ?","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"That case involved California 's Proposition 8 ban on gay marriage .","depth":5},{"id":96,"text":"If the justices choose to rule broadly ,","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"they could overturn Prop 8","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"and in doing so invalidate every other restriction on gay marriage in the country .","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"But the justices suggested Tuesday","depth":7},{"id":100,"text":"they could decide the case","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"without issuing a ruling","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"that ripples through all 50 states .","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"Several justices ,","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"including some liberals","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"who seemed open to gay marriage ,","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"raised doubts","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"that the case was properly before them .","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"Such an outcome would almost certainly allow gay marriages to resume in California","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"but would have no impact elsewhere .","depth":7},{"id":110,"text":"The justices ' statement spanned the gamut .","depth":5},{"id":111,"text":"Chief Justice John Roberts said","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"it seemed supporters of gay marriage were trying to change the meaning of the word `` marriage ''","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"by including same-sex couples .","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"Lawyers","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"representing supporters of the California ban","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"known as Proposition 8","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"argued","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"that the court should not override the democratic process","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"and impose a judicial solution","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"that would redefine marriage in the some 40 states","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"that do not allow same-sex couples to wed .","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"Americans as a whole are divided on the issue .","depth":4},{"id":123,"text":"A poll","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"released Thursday","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"showed","depth":7},{"id":126,"text":"49 percent of voters favor legalizing gay marriage ,","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"while 46 percent oppose it .","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"That marks a shift","depth":6},{"id":129,"text":"since the question was first asked in 2003","depth":7},{"id":130,"text":"-- when 32 percent said","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"gay marriage should be legal ,","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"and 58 percent opposed it .","depth":8},{"id":133,"text":"Gay marriage has been approved in nine states","depth":6},{"id":134,"text":"-- Connecticut , Iowa , Maine , Maryland , Massachusetts , New Hampshire , New York , Vermont , Washington --","depth":6},{"id":135,"text":"and the District of Columbia .","depth":5},{"id":136,"text":"But 31 states have amended their constitutions","depth":6},{"id":137,"text":"to prohibit same-sex marriage .","depth":6},{"id":138,"text":"North Carolina was the most recent example last May .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":277,"left":229,"right":276,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":229,"left":146,"right":228,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":144,"right":145,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":142,"right":143,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142,"left":140,"right":141,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":140,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":141,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":143,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":145,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":228,"left":210,"right":227,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":210,"left":182,"right":209,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":182,"left":148,"right":181,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":8,"right":147,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":181,"left":150,"right":180,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":150,"left":11,"right":149,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":149,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":180,"left":151,"right":179,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"attribution","nuclearit